The paper discusses reinforcement learning agents and their performance on difficult learning games, which suggests that it belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The proposed solution involves learning a latent representation of the environment, which could fall under robotics (cs.RO) or systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions state-of-the-art performance on visual games, indicating that computer vision (cs.CV) may also be a relevant sub-category.
